      "value": "<p>Geometry in Maya makes use of the many options available in RenderMan. To explore these in a generic discussion, take a look at their <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19661231/Geometry\" data-linked-resource-id=\"19661231\" data-linked-resource-version=\"10\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">home</a>. Below is a discussion of each of these as they are used inside of Maya. This is not an exhaustive list and will grow!</p><h3 id=\"GeometryinMaya-GeometryinMaya\">Geometry in Maya</h3><p><ul class=\"childpages-macro conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-macro-id=\"7ed93e56-4f9c-4ec6-8638-53f638c99438\" data-macro-name=\"children\"><li><a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544539634/Archives+in+Maya\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544539634\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Archives in Maya</a></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544539731/Curves+in+Maya\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544539731\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Curves in Maya</a></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544539792/Instances+in+Maya\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544539792\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Instances in Maya</a></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544539956/Particles+in+Maya\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544539956\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Particles in Maya</a></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544539991/Subdivision+Surfaces+in+Maya\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544539991\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Subdivision Surfaces in Maya</a></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544540066/OpenVDB+Volumes+in+Maya\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544540066\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">OpenVDB Volumes in Maya</a></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544540118/Aggregate+Volumes+in+Maya\" data-